.TH "batadv_send_roam_adv" 9 "batadv_send_roam_adv" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_send_roam_adv \- send a roaming advertisement message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_send_roam_adv
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "u8 *client "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_orig_node *orig_node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "client" 12
mac address of the roaming client
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN identifier
.IP "orig_node" 12
message destination
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a ROAMING_ADV message to the node which was previously serving this
client. This is done to inform the node that from now on all traffic destined
for this particular roamed client has to be forwarded to the sender of the
roaming message.
